# Update Templates to Support All 16 IELTS Question Types

The [IELTS_TEST_CREATION_GUIDE.md](file:///c:/cd-mock/IELTS_TEST_CREATION_GUIDE.md) defines **16 question types** with specific data structures and UI rendering rules. The existing templates only handle a subset. This plan upgrades both reading and listening templates to support all types, and updates the AI processor to use the guide's data model.

## Gap Analysis

### Current vs Required Question Types

| Guide Type | Internal Code | Reading | Listening | Status |
|---|---|:---:|:---:|---|
| `TRUE_FALSE_NOT_GIVEN` | `tfng` | ✅ | — | **Exists** |
| `YES_NO_NOT_GIVEN` | `ynnng` | ❌ | — | **NEW** — identical to tfng with YES/NO labels |
| `MULTIPLE_CHOICE` | `mcq` | ✅ | ✅ | **Exists** |
| `MULTIPLE_ANSWER` | `multi` | ❌ | ✅ | **NEW for reading** |
| `NOTE_COMPLETION` | `note` | ❌ | ✅ | **NEW for reading** — uses `{N}` template |
| `SENTENCE_COMPLETION` | `fill` | ✅ | — | **Exists** (rename-compatible) |
| `SUMMARY_COMPLETION` | `summary` | ❌ | — | **NEW** — paragraph with blanks |
| `SUMMARY_COMPLETION_DRAG_DROP` | `dragdrop` | ❌ | — | **NEW** — word bank + drag |
| `SHORT_ANSWER` | `short` | ❌ | ❌ | **NEW** — question + text input |
| `TABLE_COMPLETION` | `table` | ❌ | ❌ | **NEW** — renders HTML table with inputs |
| `FLOW_CHART_COMPLETION` | `flowchart` | ❌ | ❌ | **NEW** — HTML flowchart with blanks |
| `MATCHING_HEADINGS` | [select](file:///c:/cd-mock/builder.js#21-30) | ✅ | — | **Exists** (needs enhancement) |
| `MATCHING_INFORMATION` | `matchinfo` | ❌ | — | **NEW** — dropdown per statement |
| `MATCHING_FEATURES` | `matchfeat` | ❌ | ✅ | **Enhance** — uses `match` but needs dropdown |
| `MATCHING_SENTENCE_ENDINGS` | `matchend` | ❌ | — | **NEW** — sentence start + endings list |
| `DIAGRAM_LABELLING` | `diagram` | ❌ | ❌ | **NEW** — image + numbered inputs |
| `PLAN_MAP_LABELLING` | `planmap` | ❌ | ❌ | **NEW** — map image + dropdown |

### Data Structure Changes

The guide uses a **hierarchical model**: Question groups → Sub-questions + Options. The current templates use flat structures. We need to adopt the guide's data model to ensure the AI processor can output data that the templates can render.

**New unified question data structure:**
```js
{
  type: "TRUE_FALSE_NOT_GIVEN",  // guide enum
  section: "Questions 1-6",
  instruction: "...",
  questionText: "",              // optional HTML context
  headingOptions: {},            // for MATCHING_HEADINGS
  tableData: {},                 // for TABLE_COMPLETION
  questions: [                   // sub-questions
    { questionNumber: 1, questionText: "...", correctAnswer: "TRUE" }
  ],
  options: [                     // for MCQ, MULTI, DRAG_DROP, MATCH types
    { optionKey: "A", optionText: "...", isCorrect: false }
  ]
}
```

## Proposed Changes

---

### Reading Template

#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///c:/cd-mock/app.js)

**Data structure update**: Transform `TEST_DATA` to use the guide's unified structure. All question types will use the `questions[]` (sub-questions) and `options[]` pattern from [IELTS_TEST_CREATION_GUIDE.md](file:///c:/cd-mock/IELTS_TEST_CREATION_GUIDE.md).

**New renderers to add** (12 new question type handlers):
1. `ynnng` — YES/NO/NOT GIVEN (3 radio buttons, different labels from tfng)
2. `multi` — MULTIPLE_ANSWER (checkboxes from options[])
3. `note` — NOTE_COMPLETION (HTML template with `{N}` → input fields)
4. `summary` — SUMMARY_COMPLETION (paragraph with inline blanks)
5. `dragdrop` — SUMMARY_COMPLETION_DRAG_DROP (word bank + drop zones)
6. `short` — SHORT_ANSWER (question text + input)
7. `table` — TABLE_COMPLETION (rendered HTML table with input cells)
8. `flowchart` — FLOW_CHART_COMPLETION (HTML content with inputs)
9. `matchinfo` — MATCHING_INFORMATION (statement + paragraph dropdown)
10. `matchfeat` — MATCHING_FEATURES (statement + feature dropdown)
11. `matchend` — MATCHING_SENTENCE_ENDINGS (sentence start + endings dropdown)
12. `diagram` — DIAGRAM_LABELLING (image + numbered inputs)
13. `planmap` — PLAN_MAP_LABELLING (map image + options dropdown)

**Scoring update**: [submitTest()](file:///c:/cd-mock/listening.js#550-639) must handle all 16 types for correct/incorrect determination.

---

### Listening Template

#### [MODIFY] [listening.js](file:///c:/cd-mock/listening.js)

Same new renderers as reading (where applicable to listening tests). The listening template already handles `note`, `mcq`, `multi`, `match`. Additions needed:
- `ynnng`, `summary`, `dragdrop`, `short`, `table`, `flowchart`, `matchinfo`, `matchfeat`, `matchend`, `diagram`, `planmap`
- `tfng` (also possible in listening)

**Scoring update**: [submitTest()](file:///c:/cd-mock/listening.js#550-639) must handle all types.

---

### AI Processor

#### [MODIFY] [ai-processor.js](file:///c:/cd-mock/ai-processor.js)

Update system prompts for both reading and listening to:
1. Use the guide's **16 enum type names** as the `type` field
2. Output the **unified data structure** (`questions[]` + `options[]` + `headingOptions` + `tableData`)
3. Include UI rendering hints per type

---

### Template Generator

#### [MODIFY] [template-generator.js](file:///c:/cd-mock/template-generator.js)

Update data injection to map the guide's data model into the template's expected format. The generator must transform AI output (guide format) → template data format.

---

### CSS Updates

#### [MODIFY] [style.css](file:///c:/cd-mock/style.css)

Add styles for new question types: drag-and-drop zones, table completion inputs, flowchart boxes, diagram labels, matching sentence panels.

#### [MODIFY] [listening.css](file:///c:/cd-mock/listening.css)

Same new styles for listening-specific variants.

